# pat2-subtask1
//what is a Morse code
Morse code is a method of encoding text information as a series of on-off tones,clicks,or light flashes that can be used for communication over a telegraph or other communucation device. 

//why Morse code was created
Morse code,either of the system for representing letters of the alphabet,numerals, and punctuation marks by an arragement of dots, dashes, and space. The codes are transmitted as electrical pulses of varied lengths or analogous mechanical or visual signal, such as flashing lights. One of the systems was invented in the united states by American artist and inventor Samuel F.B. Morse during the 1830s for electrical telegraphy.This version was further improved by American scientists and businessman Alfred Lewis vail,Morse's assistant and patner.S
